-- Arsenal Tops Liverpool 2-1 in Premier League on Van Persie Goals
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-03-03T14:51:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-03/arsenal-tops-liverpool-2-1-in-premier-league-on-van-persie-goals.html
Robin  van Persie ’s second goal of
the game in stoppage time gave Arsenal a 2-1 win over Liverpool
in English soccer’s Premier League.  Van Persie scored in each half as Arsenal handed Liverpool
its first home loss of the season. The Dutchman leads the league
with 25 goals and has 31 total for the season.  Arsenal goalkeeper Wojciech Szczesny saved Dirk Kuyt’s
penalty kick in the first half, while Laurent Koscielny’s own
goal accounted for the Liverpool score.  The victory moves Arsenal three points ahead of Chelsea in
the race for fourth place and the final spot in the  Champions
League .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
